tranId:
Header

Enter a unique JE Entry Number in this field.
subsidiary:
HEADER

This is a reference to the subsidiary which must be created in your Setup > Company > Subsidiaries prior to import.

In case you want to refer a child subsidiary the complete hierarchy must be provided in the format: Parent Subsidiary Name : Child Subsidiary Name. 

This field becomes mandatory if you are using a NetSuite One-World account.
currency:
HEADER

This field is the currency used for all amounts in this journal entry.

For regular journal entries, currency defaults to the base currency of your company or root parent subsidiary, and can be changed to any other currency available in your account.
exchangerate:
HEADER

If the default exhange rate will not be used, enter the exchange rate for this transaction.
postingperiod:
HEADER
This element is a reference to a posting period that
must exist in your account prior to importing.
The accounting period to which the transaction is being posted to must be OPEN.
tranDate:
HEADER

Enter the date on which the JE is to be created. Date should be entered in the format that is supported by your account. 

The date preference can be set by navigating to Setup > Company > General Preferences.
reversalDate:
HEADER

Enter the date for the reversing entry to be posted. Date should be entered in the format that is supported by your account. 

The date preference can be set by navigating to Setup > Company > General Preferences.
isDeferred:
HEADER

Put TRUE if the reversal entry is to be deferred to the date specified in column G.
journalItemLine_accountRef:
LINES

This is a reference to the GL account against which the amounts have to be posted.  The complete hierarchy of the accounts should be provided if you want to refer to a child account. The expected format is Child Account Number Parent Account Name : Child Account Name.

The account must be setup in Lists > Accounting > Accounts prior to import.
journalItemLine_debitAmount:
LINES

Enter the debit amount in this field.
journalItemLine_creditAmount:
LINES

Enter the credit amount in this field.
journalItemLine_memo:
LINES

Memo for the current line item
journalItemLine_entityRef:
LINES

References an existing entity record. The entity records must exist in your account prior to importing the JE.  If the customer to be referred is a child customer, the customer ids with complete parent-child will have to be provided. 

e.g. Parent CustomerID : Child CustomerID
journalItemLine_departmentRef:
LINES



Provide the reference to the Department in this field.  In order to reference a sub department provide the complete hierarchy in the format Parent Department : Child department.

This should be created in Setup > Company > Departments prior to import.
journalItemLine_classRef:
LINES

Provide the reference to the class in this field.  In order to reference a sub class provide the complete hierarchy in the format: Parent Class : Child Class.

This should be created in Setup > Company > Classes prior to import.
journalItemLine_locationRef:
LINES

Provide the reference to the Location in this field. In order to reference a sub Location provide the complete hierarchy in the format Parent Location : Child Location.

This should be created in Setup > Company > Locations prior to import.
journalItemLine_taxCodeRef:
LINES

Reference to a Tax Code that must exist in Setup > Accounting > Tax Codes prior to import.
journalItemLine_taxCodeAmount:
LINES

Enter the Tax Amount in this field
